{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "10", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "19", "M": "12", "S": "52"}}, "news": [{"title": "Goa: TCP approves 12 conversions applications totalling 2.1 hectares across five talukas", "para": "The TCP board approved twelve private applications for land conversion. These approvals allow converting green cover into settlement zones across five talukas. Applications from a sarpanch and son involved orchard land conversion at Verna. A large plot at Podocem, Sattari, was also approved for settlement. These approvals follow a recent batch of sixteen private proposals for land conversion.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/goa-tcp-approves-12-land-conversions-across-five-talukas/132304971?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-408279/132304971.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Bhopal residents air grievances on civic issues in their colonies", "para": "Bhopal residents gathered to voice grievances about delayed housing possession and missing civic amenities. Many buyers felt cheated as developers shifted focus to new projects after making promises.  A multi-departmental Colony Cell has been formed to address these resident complaints. Officials interacted with affected people, addressing their concerns at the district collectorate auditorium.  Progress on resolving remaining issues will be reviewed by the administration after one week.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/bhopal-residents-demand-completion-of-civic-amenities-in-housing-colonies/132304854?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1437642/132304854.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "NGT directs Ghaziabad DM to prevent illegal construction in city forest", "para": "The National Green Tribunal has ordered the Ghaziabad District Magistrate to prevent illegal construction. This directive concerns the 200-acre Sai Upvan forest area, known as the city's lungs. The tribunal is hearing a case about the forest's deteriorating environmental condition. Allegations suggest the Ghaziabad Nagar Nigam is undertaking unauthorized construction within the protected zone. An interim order mandates stopping all such activities until September 16.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/national-green-tribunal-takes-action-against-illegal-construction-in-ghaziabad-forest/132304824?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1232827/132304824.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}